-- KPMG Cuts Size of German Management Board, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-03-21T17:40:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/kpmg-cuts-size-of-german-management-board-handelsblatt-reports.html
KPMG’s German unit plans to cut its
management board to five members from 16 to reduce costs,
 Handelsblatt  reported in a preview of an article to be published
tomorrow, citing unidentified people at KPMG Deutschland.  The management board of  Germany ’s second-largest accounting
firm will include Klaus Becker, Ernst Groebl, Michael Krall,
Wolfgang Zieren and Michael Kozikowski, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
